      "properties": {
        "content": "Findings describe an end-to-end test of bridging BTC into the Monad ecosystem and onward routing, documenting the operational steps and testnet tooling. Steps observed: obtaining BTC from a faucet with an EVM wallet, bridging BTC into Monad (resulting in cBTC on Monad), and then bridging that cBTC either to another chain or back to the BTC chain. Additional context references a testnet and links for the faucet and bridge, plus a note about transactions performed for Giwa (an L2 related to Upbit). This differs from other potential findings because it captures an actual round-trip bridging workflow (not just a planned integration) and supplies concrete tooling URLs and testnet usage, making it actionable for reproducing or diagnosing the bridge flow. Implications include verification of cross-chain minting (cBTC issuance on Monad), compatibility of EVM wallets with the faucet and bridge, and potential interoperability with L2 projects (Giwa). Recommended next steps: reproduce the steps, record tx hashes at each hop, validate cBTC custody and redemption back to BTC, and test edge cases (insufficient fee, nonce mismatch, cross-chain finality).",
